            <thetext>Some files can be detected as a wrong/unwanted type (see bug #6163). It would be nice to have a possibility to configure these via configuration.xml.

We can do it via -A command line switch but only by specifying suffixes (see bug #6164).

Something like this would be nice:

&lt;void property=&quot;static_classes&quot;&gt;
  &lt;void property=&quot;plain&quot;&gt;
    &lt;string&gt;README*&lt;/string&gt;
    &lt;string&gt;*.txt&lt;/string&gt;
    &lt;string&gt;usr/src/foo/*/textfiles/*&lt;/string&gt;
  &lt;/void&gt;
&lt;/void&gt;</thetext>
